Name: üßë‚Äçüíº Agency Website Domain (Example: pray.com)
Description:
This property indicates whether there is any agency associated with the deal. 

If a company associated with the deal has the ‚ÄúAgency‚Äù designation, a workflow will transfer that information from the company to this deal property. 

If there is no Agency Company associated with this deal, but there is an Agency involved in the negotiation, the operator can input the Agency Website Domain, allowing HubSpot to trigger a workflow that will create the necessary associations and establish a new company.

PS: A domain name consists of labels separated by dots.
Each label can have 1 to 63 characters, letters, numbers, or hyphens.
The last label must be 2 to 63 letters long.
Usages: Automation platform flow (2); Flow action (1); Sales view (22); Dependent conditional field (3); Properties v3 card (1); Controlling pipeline stage field (3)

Name: üßë‚Äçüíº Associated Agency Company Name

This property is synchronized with the Company Name field of the most recent company associated with this deal, which has the ‚ÄúAgency" label on it.

Name: Record ID
Description: The unique ID for this record. This value is set automatically by HubSpot.
Usages: Rollup property (5); Automation platform flow (2); Report (20); Dataset (13); Sales view (10); Goal target (16); Properties v3 card (2)

Name: Leader Name
Description:
The name of the leader as it should appear on the PRAY APP.
If a Leader is linked to the deal, a workflow will copy that information from the Leader.
- Suppose there is no Leader associated with this deal. In that case, the operator can input the leader‚Äôs name, allowing HubSpot to trigger a workflow that creates the necessary associations and establishes a new leader if one does not already exist.
Usages: Automation platform flow (14); Flow action (5); Report (2); Sales view (1); Dependent conditional field (5); Properties v3 card (3); Controlling pipeline stage field (4)

Name: Auto-Renewal
Description:
Auto-renewal indicates whether a deal (typically a subscription or contract) will automatically renew at the end of its term without requiring manual intervention or re-signing. This is represented as a binary option (e.g., "Yes" or "No") or with specific renewal terms.
Standard terms default to ‚ÄúYes.‚Äù 
If ‚ÄúNo‚Äù is negotiated, it is manually changed by a sales or customer success representative when the deal is created or updated.
Options: Yes; No
Usages: Rollup property (1); Automation platform flow (3); Dataset (3); Sales view (9); Properties v3 card (3)

Name: Billing Frequency
Description: How often a product with recurring billing is billed. It informs the pricing calculation for deals and quotes. Products with one-time billing aren‚Äôt included.
Options: Weekly (weekly); Every two weeks (biweekly); Monthly (monthly); Quarterly (quarterly); Semi-annually (per_six_months); Annually (annually); Every two years (per_two_years); Every three years (per_three_years); Every four years (per_four_years); Every five years (per_five_years)
Usages: Dataset (1); Sales view (9); Properties v3 card (1)

Name: Billing Start Date
Usages: Dataset (5); Sales view (9); Properties v3 card (2); Association v3 card (1)

Name: Closed Won Reason
Description: Reason why this deal was won
Usages: Report (1); Dataset (1); Dependent conditional field (1); Association table card (1); Properties v3 card (1); Controlling pipeline stage field (1)

Name: Leader Type
Description:
It‚Äôs a Snapshot of the type of the parent company at the moment the deal is created.
The workflow copies the information from the Parent Company -> Company Type property.
Options: Media Ministry; Mega Church; Podcaster; Other; PLG
Usages: Automation platform flow (5); Report (1); Dataset (3); Sales view (10); Dependent conditional field (3); Properties v3 card (3); Controlling pipeline stage field (3)

Name: Effective Date
Description:
The contract start date, typically the date of the last signature, is when the agreement becomes legally binding.
Data source: workflow automatically sets the date from e-signature or can be manually entered by a user.
Usages: Automation platform flow (3); Dataset (5); Sales view (10); Dependent conditional field (2); Properties v3 card (2); Controlling pipeline stage field (2)

Name: üó£Ô∏è Leader Webiste
Description:
The official website of the organization associated with the name displayed on the PRAY APP. If the artist type is a Person, this website might be separate from the parent company‚Äôs site responsible for the purchase. 
- If a Leader is linked to the deal, a workflow will copy that information from the Leader.
- Suppose there is no Leader associated with this deal. In that case, the operator can input the leader‚Äôs domain, allowing HubSpot to trigger a workflow that creates the necessary associations and establishes a new leader if one does not already exist.
Usages: Automation platform flow (3); Sales view (1); Dependent conditional field (1); Properties v3 card (1); Controlling pipeline stage field (1)
